#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn47.17"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.17:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.17:0.2"
msgid "2. Nālandavagga "
msgstr "2. At Nālandā "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.17:0.3"
msgid "17. Ariyasutta "
msgstr "17. Noble "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.167, sc1
msgctxt "sn47.17:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ariyā niyyānikā niyyanti takkarassa sammā dukkhakkhayāya. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when these four kinds of mindfulness meditation are developed and cultivated they are noble and emancipating, and bring one who practices them to the complete ending of suffering. "

msgctxt "sn47.17:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.17:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.17:1.4"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "sn47.17:1.5"
msgid "citte … pe … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "sn47.17:1.6"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.17:1.7"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ariyā niyyānikā niyyanti takkarassa sammā dukkhakkhayāyā”ti. "
msgstr "When these four kinds of mindfulness meditation are developed and cultivated they are noble and emancipating, and bring one who practices them to the complete ending of suffering.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.17:1.8"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
